## Browser Testing

Test web pages and user flows using `agent-browser` CLI. Configuration lives in `.claude/rubot/rubot.local.yaml` under `agent_browser`.

```bash
# Quick smoke test against the dev server
agent-browser open {AGENT_BROWSER_TARGET_URL}
agent-browser snapshot -i
agent-browser errors
agent-browser close

# Run full E2E test suite (reads scenarios from rubot.local.yaml)
/rubot-test-browser

# Setup agent-browser if not installed
/rubot-setup-agent-browser
```

### Core Workflow

```
1. agent-browser open <url>       # Navigate to the page
2. agent-browser snapshot -i      # Get interactive element refs (@e1, @e2)
3. agent-browser click @e1        # Interact with elements
   agent-browser fill @e2 "text"  # Fill form fields
4. agent-browser snapshot -i      # Re-snapshot after changes
5. agent-browser errors           # Check for console errors
6. agent-browser close            # Clean up
```

